
This starts the backend on port 8000.  
The desktop client cannot be run inside Docker (requires a display server).

## Important Notes

- The backend includes CORS middleware configured to allow all origins during development.
- The desktop client communicates directly with the game’s Phaser engine; no HTTP calls to the backend are used in the current vertical slice.
- Health check endpoint: `GET /health` returns `{"status": "ok"}`.
- The AI opponent selects a target (the player) and fires its equipped weapon (loaded from mission data). Its aim is currently deterministic (centre of the target). The AI logic is isolated in dedicated helper methods `getAITargets` and `getAIAimPoint`, making it straightforward to extend with different behaviours, difficulty levels, or multiple enemies.
